<article title='Transport_in_Estonia'><paragraph><bold>Transport in Estonia</bold><space/>relies mainly on road and rail networks.</paragraph><heading level='2'>Roads</heading><paragraph><link><target>File:Main roads of Estonia.svg</target><part>thumb</part><part>250px</part><part>Estonian main and E-roads</part></link></paragraph><list type='bullet'><listitem>total: 57,565&amp;nbsp;km (including 16,465 of national roads)</listitem><listitem>paved: 12,926&amp;nbsp;km (including 99&amp;nbsp;km of<space/><link><target>limited-access road</target><trail>s</trail></link>)</listitem></list><heading level='3'>National roads</heading><paragraph>National roads form the core of Estonian road network. Their total length is 16,489&amp;nbsp;km (or 28% of all roads), 67% of them are paved.<extension extension_name='ref'><template><target>cite web</target><arg name="url">http://www.mnt.ee/failid/MNT_Aastaraamat2013_eng.pdf<space/></arg><arg name="title">Annual Report 2013<space/></arg><arg name="publisher">Estonian Road Administration<space/></arg><arg name="accessdate">2013-12-19</arg></template></extension><space/>They are divided into 4 classes according to importance:</paragraph><list type='bullet'><listitem>main roads (1,607&amp;nbsp;km)</listitem><listitem>basic roads (2,406&amp;nbsp;km)</listitem><listitem>secondary roads (12,476&amp;nbsp;km)</listitem><listitem>local roads (18,455&amp;nbsp;km)</listitem></list><paragraph><template><target>-</target></template></paragraph><table class="wikitable sortable"><tablecaption><bold>Main roads</bold></tablecaption><tablerow><tablehead>Number</tablehead><tablehead><link><target>International E-road network</target><part>E-road</part></link></tablehead><tablehead class="unsortable">Route</tablehead><tablehead>Length (km)</tablehead><tablehead class="unsortable">Notes</tablehead></tablerow><tablerow><tablecell><template><target>estonian road number sign</target><arg>1</arg></template></tablecell><tablecell><template><target>European 